# Build Configuration Guide

This document explains the structure and configuration of the `build.gradle.kts` file in the GAP Library Template.

## File Structure Overview

The build script is organized into logical sections for maintainability and clarity:

```kotlin
// 1. PLUGINS - All plugin declarations
// 2. PROJECT CONFIGURATION - Basic project settings
// 3. REPOSITORIES - Dependency sources
// 4. GAP PLUGIN CONFIGURATION - GAP-specific settings
// 5. DEPENDENCIES - Library dependencies
// 6. JAVA & KOTLIN CONFIGURATION - Language settings
// 7. TESTING CONFIGURATION - Test framework setup
// 8. CODE QUALITY CONFIGURATION - Static analysis and coverage
// 9. BUILD TASK CONFIGURATION - JAR and build customization
// 10. DOCUMENTATION CONFIGURATION - API docs setup
```

## Section Details

### 1. Plugins

```kotlin
plugins {
    // Core plugins for Kotlin library development
    alias(libs.plugins.kotlin)
    id("java-library")
    
    // Quality and documentation tools
    alias(libs.plugins.dokka)
    alias(libs.plugins.detekt)
    id("jacoco")
    
    // Modern testing framework
    id("jvm-test-suite")
    
    // GAP ecosystem integration
    id("au.com.pexa.gap.versioning-publishing") version "1.0.0-SNAPSHOT"
}
```

**Key Features:**
- Uses version catalog (`libs.plugins.*`) for consistent versioning
- GAP plugin provides automated versioning and publishing
- Modern test suite plugin for better test organization

### 2. Project Configuration

```kotlin
group = "au.com.pexa.gap"
```

**Template Variables:**
- This will be updated by the setup script based on your package structure

### 3. Repositories

```kotlin
repositories {
    mavenCentral()
    
    maven {
        name = "PEXAArtifactory"
        url = uri("https://pexaartifacts.jfrog.io/artifactory/libs-release-local")
        credentials(PasswordCredentials::class) {
            username = System.getenv("ARTIFACTORY_USER") ?: System.getProperty("artifactory.user")
            password = System.getenv("ARTIFACTORY_PASSWORD") ?: System.getProperty("artifactory.password")
        }
        authentication {
            create<BasicAuthentication>("basic")
        }
    }
}
```

**Features:**
- Maven Central for public dependencies
- PEXA Artifactory for internal libraries
- Secure credential handling via environment variables

### 4. GAP Plugin Configuration

```kotlin
gapVersioning {
    versionFile = "version.txt"
    enableVersionChecking = true
    generateBuildConfig = true
    buildConfigPackage = "au.com.pexa.gap.buildconfig"
    artifactoryUrl = "https://pexaartifacts.jfrog.io/artifactory/libs-release-local"
}
```

**Capabilities:**
- Automatic version resolution from `version.txt`
- BuildConfig generation for runtime version access
- Version existence checking to prevent duplicates
- Integrated publishing to Artifactory

### 5. Dependencies

```kotlin
dependencies {
    // Kotlin standard libraries
    implementation(libs.kotlinStdlib)
    implementation(libs.kotlinReflect)

    // Logging framework
    implementation(libs.slf4j)

    // JSON processing
    implementation(libs.jacksonDatabind)
    implementation(libs.jacksonKotlin)
}
```

**Design Principles:**
- Uses version catalog for dependency management
- Includes common libraries needed by most GAP libraries
- Test dependencies are configured separately in the testing block

### 6. Java & Kotlin Configuration

```kotlin
java {
    toolchain {
        languageVersion.set(JavaLanguageVersion.of(21))
    }
    withJavadocJar()
    withSourcesJar()
}

kotlin {
    jvmToolchain(21)
}

tasks.withType<KotlinCompile>().configureEach {
    compilerOptions {
        jvmTarget.set(org.jetbrains.kotlin.gradle.dsl.JvmTarget.JVM_21)
        freeCompilerArgs.addAll(
            "-opt-in=kotlin.RequiresOptIn",
            "-Xjsr305=strict"
        )
    }
}
```

**Features:**
- Java 21 toolchain for consistent builds
- Automatic generation of sources and javadoc JARs
- Enhanced Kotlin compiler options for better code quality

### 7. Testing Configuration

```kotlin
testing {
    suites {
        val test by getting(JvmTestSuite::class) {
            useJUnitJupiter()
            
            dependencies {
                implementation(platform("org.junit:junit-bom:5.10.1"))
                implementation(libs.junitApi)
                runtimeOnly(libs.junitEngine)
                implementation(libs.junitParams)
                implementation(libs.mockitoCore)
                implementation(libs.assertj)
            }
            
            targets {
                all {
                    testTask.configure {
                        jvmArgs = listOf(
                            "--add-opens", "java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED"
                        )
                        useJUnitPlatform()
                        testLogging {
                            events("passed", "skipped", "failed")
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

**Benefits:**
- Modern JVM test suite API
- JUnit 5 with comprehensive testing libraries
- Java 21 compatibility configuration
- Enhanced test logging

### 8. Code Quality Configuration

```kotlin
// Static analysis
detekt {
    buildUponDefaultConfig = true
    allRules = false
    config.setFrom("$projectDir/config/detekt.yml")
    ignoreFailures = false
}

// Code coverage
jacoco {
    toolVersion = "0.8.12"
}

tasks.jacocoTestCoverageVerification {
    violationRules {
        rule {
            limit {
                minimum = "0.80".toBigDecimal() // 80% coverage minimum
            }
        }
    }
}
```

**Quality Gates:**
- Detekt for static code analysis
- JaCoCo for code coverage measurement
- Configurable coverage thresholds
- Multiple report formats for CI/CD integration

### 9. Build Task Configuration

```kotlin
tasks.named<Jar>("sourcesJar") {
    duplicatesStrategy = DuplicatesStrategy.EXCLUDE
    archiveClassifier.set("sources")
}

tasks.named<Jar>("jar") {
    manifest {
        attributes(
            "Implementation-Title" to project.name,
            "Implementation-Version" to project.version,
            "Implementation-Vendor" to "PEXA"
        )
    }
}
```

**Enhancements:**
- Proper JAR manifest with metadata
- Duplicate handling for source JARs
- Professional artifact configuration

### 10. Documentation Configuration

```kotlin
tasks.withType<org.jetbrains.dokka.gradle.DokkaTask>().configureEach {
    dokkaSourceSets {
        named("main") {
            moduleName.set(project.name)
            includes.from("docs/api.md")
        }
    }
}
```

**Features:**
- Dokka for API documentation generation
- Configurable documentation includes
- Professional documentation output

## Customization Guide

### Adding Dependencies

```kotlin
dependencies {
    // Add your dependencies here
    implementation("com.example:library:1.0.0")
    
    // Or use version catalog
    implementation(libs.yourLibrary)
}
```

### Adjusting Code Quality

```kotlin
// Adjust coverage threshold
tasks.jacocoTestCoverageVerification {
    violationRules {
        rule {
            limit {
                minimum = "0.90".toBigDecimal() // 90% coverage
            }
        }
    }
}

// Customize Detekt rules
detekt {
    config.setFrom("$projectDir/config/custom-detekt.yml")
}
```

### Adding Test Suites

```kotlin
testing {
    suites {
        val integrationTest by registering(JvmTestSuite::class) {
            useJUnitJupiter()
            
            dependencies {
                implementation(project())
                // Add integration test specific dependencies
            }
        }
    }
}
```

## Best Practices

1. **Keep sections organized** - Don't mix configuration types
2. **Use version catalogs** - Centralize dependency versions
3. **Document custom configurations** - Add comments for complex setups
4. **Test your changes** - Always run `./gradlew build` after modifications
5. **Follow GAP standards** - Use the GAP plugin for versioning and publishing

## Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

1. **Build fails after changes**: Run `./gradlew clean build`
2. **Dependency resolution issues**: Check version catalog and repository configuration
3. **Test failures**: Verify JVM arguments and test dependencies
4. **Coverage failures**: Adjust thresholds or improve test coverage

### Getting Help

- Check the main README.md for general guidance
- Review VERSIONING.md for GAP plugin details
- Use `./gradlew help --task <taskname>` for task-specific help
- Consult Gradle documentation for advanced configurations
